2. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The paper deals with a decentralized energy market, which involves multiple agents interacting with each other. This makes cs.MA a likely sub-category.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with system-level grid constraints, which is a topic related to systems and control. This makes cs.SY a likely sub-category.
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a distributed algorithm to converge to the GNE, which involves optimization and learning. This makes cs.LG a possible sub-category.
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper deals with designing a decentralized energy market, which involves computational methods and optimization. This makes cs.CE a possible sub-category.
